The paper presents a novel translation of UML class diagrams to Alloy, which is a formal specification language used for software analysis. This work involves software engineering (SE) and programming languages (PL) as it deals with the translation of one modeling language to another. It also involves logic (LO) as it uses Alloy, which is a logic-based language. Additionally, it involves database (DB) as it deals with the analysis of object models. Finally, it involves artificial intelligence (AI) as it uses a deeper embedding strategy to enable solving several analysis problems.
